Class: i've put more hours into optimizing my inventory space in this game than i have into actually playing the main quest. it's like they intentionally made it a tetris minigame
Recall: it's just slightly different shades of brown armor and crafting materials. seriously
F1-Score: i spend half my time comparing weights and values like i'm prepping for a post-apocalyptic garage sale. and don't even get me started on the crafting system – i swear
column8: you need a phd in virtual botany and a minor in advanced alchemy. the story is okay
column10: but good luck remembering it between inventory management sessions. worth it? maybe
column11: if you enjoy digital spreadsheet simulators disguised as rpgs.
